<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title><%= title %> · Express Starter Lab</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #0f172a;
        --bg-card: #0b1220;
        --accent: #38bdf8;
        --accent-soft: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12);
        --text: #e5e7eb;
        --text-muted: #9ca3af;
        --border: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.25);
        --shadow-soft: 0 18px 45px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.75);
        --radius-xl: 18px;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
          sans-serif;
        background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #1d283a 0, #020617 55%);
        color: var(--text);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .nav {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 16px 24px;
      }

      .nav-inner {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 1040px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 16px;
      }

      .nav-logo {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.03em;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }

      .nav-logo-badge {
        width: 24px;
        height: 24px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--accent);
        background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 0, #0ea5e9 0, #020617 55%);
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 18px;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      .nav-links a {
        color: var(--text-muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        padding: 6px 10px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid transparent;
        transition: all 0.18s ease-out;
      }

      .nav-links a:hover {
        color: var(--text);
        border-color: var(--border);
        background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.8);
      }

      .nav-links a.primary {
        color: var(--accent);
        border-color: var(--accent-soft);
        background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.9);
      }

      main {
        flex: 1;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 12px 16px 32px;
      }

      .shell {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 1040px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 3fr);
        margin-top: 10px;
      }

      @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .shell {
          grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 3fr) minmax(0, 2fr);
          gap: 32px;
          align-items: stretch;
        }
      }

      .card {
        background: linear-gradient(
            to bottom right,
            rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.88),
            rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.98)
          );
        border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
        padding: 28px 26px 24px;
      }

      .card-header-kicker {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        padding: 4px 10px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft);
        background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, #0ea5e9 0, #020617 65%);
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: #e0f2fe;
      }

      .card-header-kicker-dot {
        width: 7px;
        height: 7px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: #22c55e;
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.32);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 18px 0 8px;
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 2.7vw, 2.4rem);
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      }

      .subtitle {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        max-width: 42rem;
      }

      .section-title {
        margin-top: 24px;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: #bae6fd;
      }

      .section-body {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      .section-body p {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .stack-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 18px 0 0;
        display: grid;
        gap: 12px;
        font-size: 0.86rem;
      }

      .stack-item {
        padding: 10px 12px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(51, 65, 85, 0.85);
        background: radial-gradient(
          circle at top left,
          rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.14),
          rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.98)
        );
      }

      .stack-item-title {
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: #bae6fd;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .stack-item-body {
        color: var(--text-muted);
        line-height: 1.4;
      }

      .pill-row {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 18px;
        gap: 8px;
      }

      .pill {
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        padding: 4px 10px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        color: var(--text-muted);
        background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.85);
      }

      footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 10px 0 16px;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="nav">
      <div class="nav-inner">
        <div class="nav-logo">
          <div class="nav-logo-badge">ZT</div>
          <span>Zero-Trust Lab · Test App</span>
        </div>
        <nav class="nav-links">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <a href="/about" class="primary">About</a>
          <a href="/status">Status</a>
          <a href="/protected">Protected</a>
          <a href="/api/health">Health API</a>
          <a href="/debug/headers">Debug Headers</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <div class="shell">
        <section class="card">
          <div class="card-header-kicker">
            <span class="card-header-kicker-dot"></span>
            Architecture · What this lab demonstrates
          </div>

          <h1>About this Express Starter Lab</h1>

          <p class="subtitle">
            This environment is designed as a compact playground for modern
            application delivery: Express.js on AWS EC2, secured with
            Cloudflare Tunnel, and fully provisioned via Terraform.
          </p>

          <div class="section-title">Goals</div>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              The primary purpose of this lab is to explore how traditional
              compute (EC2) can be combined with modern Zero-Trust patterns.
              Instead of exposing EC2 directly to the internet, all external
              traffic is routed through Cloudflare Tunnel.
            </p>
            <p>
              It also serves as a reference for:
              infrastructure-as-code workflows, user-data bootstrapping,
              and simple Node.js service design.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="section-title">What’s included</div>
          <ul class="stack-list">
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">Express.js application</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                A minimal but structured Express app with multiple routes and
                EJS views (<code>/</code>, <code>/about</code>,
                <code>/status</code>, and <code>/api/health</code>).
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">AWS EC2 + user-data</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                An Ubuntu EC2 instance that bootstraps itself on first boot:
                installs Node.js, clones the repo, installs dependencies,
                configures systemd services, and starts the app.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">Cloudflare Tunnel integration</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                The instance runs <code>cloudflared</code> as a service using a
                tunnel token injected from Terraform, enabling outbound-only
                connectivity to Cloudflare Edge.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">Terraform-managed configuration</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                EC2, key pair, security group, and user-data are all defined in
                Terraform, enabling repeatable, version-controlled infrastructure
                changes.
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="pill-row">
            <span class="pill">Good for: lab demos</span>
            <span class="pill">Good for: Zero-Trust experiments</span>
            <span class="pill">Good for: Terraform + cloud-init patterns</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <aside class="card">
          <div class="section-title">Next steps</div>
          <div class="section-body">
            <p>
              You can extend this lab by adding authentication at the edge via
              Cloudflare Access, building additional API routes, or attaching a
              database (RDS, DynamoDB, etc.).
            </p>
            <p>
              It can also be adapted into a production starter for internal
              tools or private admin dashboards.
            </p>
          </div>

          <ul class="stack-list">
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">Explore status</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                Visit the <code>/status</code> page to see live runtime
                information about the app, including uptime and Node.js
                version.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="stack-item">
              <div class="stack-item-title">Check health API</div>
              <div class="stack-item-body">
                Use <code>/api/health</code> as a simple readiness endpoint for
                upstream checks or monitoring.
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
      Express Starter · Zero-Trust Lab · Powered by Node.js, AWS & Cloudflare
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
